node.text:
This weekend’s @greattnairshow was our fifth show of the 2021 Show Season. Country music, great cooking and Thunderbirds air shows - what more could you have asked for this weekend? 

We’re headed home for a week to get some practice in and to spend time with our families before we head off to Ocean City for the @ocairshow June 19-20. See you soon, Maryland! 🇺🇸

node.text:
Our @usaf_thunderbird_maintainers have completed their first-ever local conversion of an F-16 Fighting Falcon, Tail Number A91-0470.

This process saved time, money, and manpower as well as reduced the completion time by more than 100 days.

For years the maintenance team has had the capabilities to convert a traditional gray F-16 to a Thunderbirds F-16 and in October 2020, the team moved forward with that effort.

An enlisted maintenance team was developed and assigned to the project with one mission... to convert 470.

212 days later, on May 5, 2021, they succeeded.

node.title: Thunderbirds accelerate change with first-ever F-16 conversion

node.text:
For more than 65 years we have made it a point to perform in Cheyenne, Wyoming. Unfortunately, we will not be able to make it this year. We wish @fewarrenafb a safe and successful show. 

Stay safe, we cannot wait to see you all next year!

For more information about the cancellation, check out our story.

node.text:
and a culture of inclusiveness and belonging across our Air Force.

I don't have the answers, but I do know there is no room for bigotry, hatred or small mindedness in our force. Period. Every member of our team needs to know we have their back.

So let's start the conversation acknowledging we have many valued Airmen who live and work for One Nation under God, indivisible ... but for them ... without liberty and justice for all.” -Gen. David Goldfein / Chief of Staff, U.S. Air Force

node.title: “It is time for every one of us to strive for understanding

node.text:
Friday’s flyover of San Diego and Los Angeles was dedicated to the healthcare workers, first responders, military and essential employees battling COVID-19 in California. ⁣
⁣
It also served as our final mission for #AmericaStrong. It was an honor to partner with the @usnavyblueangels to salute frontline responders across the U.S. during this difficult time in our nation. ⁣
⁣
Stay healthy and stay tuned for team updates! ————————————————⁣

node.text:
Friday’s flyover of San Diego and Los Angeles was dedicated to the healthcare workers, first responders, military and essential employees battling COVID-19 in California. 
It also served as our final mission for #AmericaStrong. It was an honor to partner with the @blueangels to salute frontline responders across the U.S. during this difficult time it our nation. 
Stay healthy and stay tuned for team updates! ————————————————
#InThisTogether #aviation #military #airforce #instagramaviation #instaaviation #aviation #aviationdaily #avgeek #planespotting #instaplane #fighterjet #aviationphotography

Next stop: Ypsilanti, Michigan for the @thunderovermichigan air show!

node.text:
As we get ready to hit the road for @chefrontierdays next week, we look back on some Thunderbird history! 

#didyouknow - Cheyenne Frontier Days was our first civilian air show back in 1953?! At the time, the team was flying the F-84G Thunderjet!✈️ 

Since then, Cheyenne Frontier Days has been a huge part of every era of our demonstration!

Which era of jets was your favorite and why?
@usairforce @airmanmagazine
